<h2>
    Serif and Sans-Serif
</h2>
<p>
    Serif fonts have little marks on the ends of each line. Sans-Serif fonts 
    do not have these lines. 
</p>

<p style="font-size: 30px; font-family: serif;">
    Hi, I'm serif
</p>
<p style="font-size: 30px; font-family: sans-serif;">
    Hi, I'm sans-serif
</p>
<p>
    The sans-serif font has no points or tips on the edges of the lines, like on 
    the ends of the H's. Serif, however, has little points where the H touches the top 
    and bottom. 
</p>

