<h2>
    Web Fonts
</h2>
<p>
    Web fonts come from websites like google fonts. They can be linked in 
    the head of the document or can be used with the <code>font-face</code> ruleset in 
    the style sheet. This uses local, downloaded files. These files have different formats: 
    <ul>
        <li>
            OTF (Open Type Font)
        </li>
        <li>
            TTF (True Type Font)
        </li>
        <li>
            WOFF (Web Open Font Format)
        </li>
        <li>
            WOFF2 (Web Open Font Format 2)
        </li>
    </ul>
</p>

<p>
    Then, to reference the files in the css stylesheet, use:
    <pre><code class="lang-css">@@font-face {
  font-family: 'MyFontName';
  src: url('fonts/exampleFont.woff2') format('woff2'),
       url('fonts/exampleFont.woff') format('woff'),
       url('fonts/exampleFont.ttf') format('truetype');
}</code></pre>
</p>

<p>
    The font <code>'MyFontName'</code> is now available to use inside the stylesheet. 
</p>
<pre><code class="lang-css">p {
    font-family: 'MyFontName', sans-serif;;
}</code></pre>